### Step 5 — Admin UI Component
**New file:** `src/app/admin/projects/[id]/AdminApprovalPanel.tsx`

`'use client'` component receiving `project` (with `admin_approved`, `approved_by_admin`, `status`, and joined `approver` name).

Render logic:
- **Status is `final_review`, not yet approved:** Show `"Give Final Approval"` button (calls `giveAdminApproval`) + `"Approve & Finalize"` button (calls `adminApproveAndFinalize`). Badge: `Pending Admin Approval` (orange).
- **Status is `final_review`, approved:** Show `"Finalize Project"` button (calls `updateProject({status:'completed'})` via existing action, or a thin wrapper) + `"Revoke Approval"` button (calls `revokeAdminApproval`). Badge: `Approved by {approver.full_name}` (green).
- **Status is `completed`:** Show `"Revoke Approval"` button. Badge: `Approved by {approver.full_name}` (green).

Use `useTransition()` + `isPending` on buttons. Inline styles matching `project_dashboard_design` memory (dark surfaces, teal accent).

**Wire into:** `src/app/admin/projects/[id]/page.tsx` — render `<AdminApprovalPanel project={project} />` in the Overview tab's details panel when `project.status` is `final_review` or `completed`.

